<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861217-0120 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:McGraw-Hill Inc.</HL><DD> 12/17/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS MHP </IN><DATELINE> MCGRAW-HILL INC.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Edward T. Reilly was named president of McGraw-Hill Broadcasting Co., a New York-based unit of this publishing and business information company. Mr. Reilly, 40 years old, had been executive vice president and chief operating officer of the unit, which owns four television stations. He succeeds Donald L. Fruehling, 55, who remains an executive vice president of the parent, in charge of publishing operations, of which the broadcasting unit is a part. </TEXT></DOC>